{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Astakhov Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Astakhov Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|70|45|S|163|21|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Ob' Bay]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Astakhov Glacier''' ({{coord|70|45|S|163|21|E|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is the [[glacier]] next south of [[Chugunov Glacier]] in the [[Explorers Range]], [[Bowers Mountains]]. It flows northeast from [[Mount Hager]] and enters [[Ob' Bay]] just west of [[Platypus Ridge]], the glacier is situated in [[Victoria Land]], [[Antarctica]]. It was mapped by the [[United States Geological Survey]] from surveys and from [[U.S. Navy]] air photos, 1960&ndash;65, and named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for [[Petr Astakhov]], Soviet exchange scientist at the U.S. [[South Pole Station]] in 1967. The glacier lies on the Pennell Coast, a portion of Antarctica lying between [[Cape Williams]] and [[Cape Adare]].
