'''Brandau Glacier''' ({{Coord|84|54|S|173|30|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a wide tributary [[glacier]], {{convert|15|nmi|km}} long, flowing westward from an ice divide between [[Haynes Table]] and [[Husky Heights]] to enter [[Keltie Glacier]] just west of [[Ford Spur]]. It was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for Lieutenant Commander [[James F. Brandau]], [[U.S. Navy]], a pilot with Squadron [[VX-6]], [[Operation Deepfreeze]] 1964 and 1965.<ref name=gnis/>

