'''Crivitz''' is an [[impact crater]] on [[Mars]].  It is named after the small town of [[Crivitz]] in western [[Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]], [[Germany]]. The crater has a diameter of 6.1 kilometers and is located at 14.5 deg south and 174.7 deg east, within the larger crater [[Gusev (Mars crater)|Gusev]].

The name was proposed by Stephan Gehrke in 2002, at the time a research associate of the [[TU Berlin]] working on cartographic software and a visiting researcher at the [[United States Geological Survey]].  

