'''Haystack Catena''' ('''Haystack Vallis''' until March 2013) is a [[Crater chain|catena]] at 4.7° N, 46.2° W on [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]]. It superficially resembles a [[graben]] but is a chain of overlapping [[secondary crater]]s.<ref>[https://astrogeology.usgs.gov/Projects/PlanetaryMapping/DIGGEOL/mercury/h6/h6.pdf H-6 text_all.word<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041102102833/http://astrogeology.usgs.gov/Projects/PlanetaryMapping/DIGGEOL/mercury/h6/h6.pdf |date=November 2, 2004 }}</ref> It was named after [[Haystack Observatory]].

