{{Infobox scientist | name = Josef Penninger | image = Josef_Penninger.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1964|09|05}}<ref name="PresseCanada" /> | birth_place = [[Gurten, Upper Austria]] | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = | awards = {{Plainlist| * [[Descartes Prize]] (2006) * [[Ernst Jung Prize]] (2007) * [[Wittgenstein-Preis]] (2014) }} | workplaces = {{Plainlist| * [[Amgen]] * [[University of Toronto]] * [[Institute of Molecular Biotechnology]] * [[University of British Columbia]] }} | alma_mater = {{Plainlist| * [[University of Innsbruck]] }} | thesis_title = Phenotypical and functional analysis of intrathymic nurse (TCN)-Lymphocytes | thesis_url = | thesis_year = 1990 | doctoral_advisor = Georg Wick<ref name="MSN2018" /> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = | footnotes = | spouse = <!--(or | spouses = )--> | children = | death_cause = | education = | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | homepage = https://www.imba.oeaw.ac.at/research/josef-penninger/ }}
'''Josef Penninger''' (born 5 September 1964) is an Austrian biomedical researcher specialising in molecular [[immunology]]. He is the scientific director of the [[Institute of Molecular Biotechnology]] located at the [[Vienna Biocenter]]. In February 2018, he announced his decision to leave Vienna and become the head of the Life Sciences Institute of the [[University of British Columbia]] in [[Vancouver]], British Columbia, Canada.<ref name="PresseCanada">{{cite web | title=Genetiker Josef Penninger kehrt Wien den Rücken | language=de | url = https://diepresse.com/home/science/5366356/Genetiker-Josef-Penninger-kehrt-Wien-den-Ruecken | access-date=2018-02-19 | website = Die Presse | date = 2018-02-05}}</ref><ref name="MSN2018">{{cite web | title=Top-Forscher Josef Penninger verlässt Österreich | website=MSN | date=2018-02-19 | url=https://www.msn.com/de-at/nachrichten/wissenschaft/top-forscher-josef-penninger-verl%C3%A4sst-%C3%B6sterreich/ar-BBIIjcl | language=de | access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref>
The asteroid 48801 Penninger is named in his honour.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://minorplanetcenter.net/db_search/show_object?utf8=%E2%9C%93&object_id=48801|title=(48801) Penninger = 1997 UC1 = 1999 CT110|website=IAU Minor Planet Center}}</ref>
