{{biologist-stub}}

'''Kodimangalam S. Ravichandran''' is the chair of the Department of Microbiology at the [[University of Virginia School of Medicine]] and director of the UVA Center for Cell Clearance. He studies [[apoptosis]] in relation to many models of human disease.

He received a BVSc in Veterinary Medicine from [[Madras Veterinary College]] in India, followed by a PhD in Molecular and Cell Biology from the [[University of Massachusetts]] and did a postdoc in immunology at [[Dana-Farber Cancer Institute]].<ref name="virginia.edu">{{cite web|url=https://med.virginia.edu/faculty/faculty-listing/kr4h/|title=Ravichandran, Kodi S.|website=med.virginia.edu}}</ref> Before joining the faculty at UVA in 1996, he worked as an instructor at [[Harvard Medical School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsroom.uvahealth.com/about/news-room/archives/kodi-s.-ravichandran-phd-appointed-chair-of-the-school-of-medicine-department-of-microbiology|title=Kodi S. Ravichandran, PhD, appointed chair of the School of Medicine Department of Microbiology — UVA Health|first=|last=admin|website=newsroom.uvahealth.com}}</ref>

As of 2016, he has published more than 100 papers, with more than 10 in [[Nature (journal)|Nature]].<ref name="virginia.edu"/> He received the Governor's Award for Science Innovation in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/news/report/top-honour-for-2-indian-american-scientists/20110301.htm|title=Top honour for 2 Indian American scientists|publisher=}}</ref> In 2016, he won the Odysseus 1 Award from the Research Foundation Flanders (FWO) in Belgium, which provided over $8 million in funding for establishing a lab at [[Ghent University]]’s Vlaams Institute for Biotechnology. He will split his time between the two institutions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news.virginia.edu/content/uva-microbiologist-expands-his-research-across-atlantic|title=UVA Microbiologist Expands His Research Across the Atlantic|date=16 November 2016|publisher=}}</ref>

